						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the maṇḍapa to the left of the northern entrance (below) of the Saṅgamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 13th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states that Vibhūti Gaura, born at Māchirājapalli near Oruṁgal residing on the top of the Śrī-giri, a servant of the house of Śrī Paṇḍitārādhya solicits god's protection.</p>						

						</summary>
